==English==

===Etymology===
Seems to have been used in Ireland in the early 20th century

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A stout leather [[strap]] reinforced internally with whalebone or even lead and used to inflict [[punishment]] - especially by using it to strike against the open uplifted hands on schoolboys.
#:''The soutane (priests cassock) sleeve swished again as the pandybat was lifted and a loud crashing sound and a fierce maddening...pain made his hand shrink together...'' (Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man - James Joyce- 1916)

